The first column  tells us whether we are looking at afile or a directory e.g drwxr-xr-x
if there is a d it is a directroy (alos colour coded) . rwx is read write execute, it could be missing (-rw-). thirsd colums shows the owener of the file, e.g. kali. 4th, fifth and 6th values of the first colum (r-x for example) shows what the owner can do to this file, e.g. in this one kali can read and execute but cannot wrtie, and the last three values are for what all other users can do, for this example, the last three are also r-x so all other useers can read, and execute.

echo 'Hello' > hello.txt
ls -la/   # --> -rw-rw-r--   we do not have execute eprmission
clear screen
chmod +rwx hello.txt #change mode, adds rwx
